#{{computer science}} The distance between two [[string]]s, (think degree of misspelling). The hamming distance is the string distance for strings of the same length. Levenshtein distance is for strings of different length and is a superset of hamming distance but allows insertions.
#:''The string distance between 'here' and 'there' is 1 (insertion of a t).''

